    {
        " results in a double-hexagonally close-packed structure . Applying higher pressure of the order of hundreds or thousands of kilobars induces a series of phase transformations, in particular with a ": null
    },
    {
        "tetragonal": "Tetragonal Crystal System"
    },
    {
        " phase appearing at about 900  kbar. In one study, the dhcp phase could be produced without compression, using a nonequilibrium annealing regime with a rapid temperature change between about 400 and 700  °C, confirming the transient character of this samarium phase. Also, thin films of samarium obtained by vapor deposition may contain the hcp or dhcp phases at ambient conditions.     Samarium  are ": null
