        "– allows enhancing their transition temperature to 56  K, which is the highest value achieved so far in this series.        Freshly prepared samarium has a silvery luster. In air, it slowly oxidizes at room temperature and spontaneously ignites at 150  °C. Even when stored under ": null
    },
